<plot>It has been 75 years since the debut of the giant ape "King Kong". Even today, people still look back at this classic as a groundbreaking film that never grows old. Released in 1933, "King Kong" was the first of its kind to create larger-than-life monsters using stop-motion animation. The realism astounded many and kept American audiences entertained for years to come. Join our intrepid group as they seek out some of Hollywood's greatest names to find out why "King Kong" has remained an icon of cinema for 75 years.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?292418</url></doc>
